==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Class day
<hw>Class day</hw>. <def>In American colleges and universities, a day of
the commencement season on which the senior class celebrates the
completion of its course by exercises conducted by the members, such as
the reading of the class histories and poem, the delivery of the class
oration, the planting of the class ivy, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

